Reuters is reporting that Basil Read’s construction division has been experiencing cash flow difficulties for some time. JOHANNESBURG - Construction company Basil Read has been placed in business rescue. Reuters is reporting that Basil Read’s construction division has for some time been experiencing cash flow difficulties. The company is involved in mining and the construction of roads and buildings. Reuters is reporting that Basil Read construction has been advised that the majority of a consortium of lenders is not prepared to make bridge funding available to the company. As a result, Basil Read has stated that it will be facing circumstances constituting "financial distress". It has therefore appointed business rescue practitioners to help. Basil Read has also advised its holding company that it's taking this action. (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)